properties.NAME: Wangchuck Centennial Park
properties.DESCRIPT:
It was launched on 12 December 2008 as a tribute to the
visionary, selfless leadership of the Wangchuck dynasty.

properties.NAME: Bumdeling Wildlife Sanctuary
properties.DESCRIPT: The sanctuary has been identified as an Important Bird Area by BirdLife International because it supports black-necked cranes (it is one of the country's two wintering sites), wood snipes and grey-crowned prinias.

properties.NAME: Thrumshingla National Park
properties.DESCRIPT: According to the ministry of agriculture the garden, to be formally known as "In Situ Rhododendron Garden", will "showcase" Bhutan's rhododendron diversity in their natural habitat.

properties.NAME: Jigme Singye Wangchuck National
properties.Dzongkhag: Trongsa, Tsirang, Sarpang, Wangdue Phodrang, Zhemgang
properties.DESCRIPT: JSWNP represents the best example of the mid-Himalayan ecosystems of the Eastern Himalaya that contain several ecological biomes ranging from subtropical forests at lower altitudes to alpine meadows at their highest altitudes.

properties.NAME: Jomotsangkha Wildlife Sanctuary
properties.DESCRIPT: formerly Khaling Wildlife Sanctuary is the smallest protected area of Bhutan

properties.NAME: Jigme Dorji National Park
properties.Key Species: Tiger, Red Panda, Himalayan Black Bear
properties.DESCRIPT: named after the late Jigme Dorji Wangchuck, is the second-largest National Park of Bhutan.

properties.NAME: Jigme Khesar Strict Nature Reserve
properties.DESCRIPT: This is the only protected area in Bhutan without permanent human settlements, except for few migratory Yak herding communities.

properties.NAME: Sakteng Wildlife Sanctuary
properties.DESCRIPT: This was created to protect migoi a yeti like cryptid whose existence has not been scientifically confirmed but in which local population strong believes. Migoi are believed to haunt the northen part of area.

properties.NAME: Phipsoo Wildlife Sanctuary
properties.DESCRIPT: It wa sestablished as reserved forest in the year 1974 but later got upgraded to wildlife sanctuary in the year 1993.

properties.NAME: Royal Manas National Park
properties.Key Species: Royal Bengal Tiger, Elephant, Golden Langur
properties.DESCRIPT: It is Bhutan's oldest national park, and the Royal government considers it the "conservation showpiece of the Kingdom" and a "genetic depository" for valuable plants.
